abstract: The former mayor answered a question from a French television journalist about how he planned to win.
snippet: The former mayor answered a question from a French television journalist about how he planned to win.
lead_paragraph: OELWEIN — The quadrennial invasion of Iowa by out-of-state college students, busloads of tour groups and the foreign press is in full effect and Pete Buttigieg is happy to oblige.
headline_main: Pete Buttigieg answers French reporter’s question, in French.

abstract: Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bailey.
snippet: Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bail...
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bailey.
headline_main: Democrat Warren Sends Star Stand-In to Iowa: Her Dog Bailey
headline_print_headline: Democrat Warren Sends Star Stand-In to Iowa: Her Dog Bailey

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates promised voters in Iowa on Saturday they would unify the party to take on President Donald Trump even as they kept up their criticism of each other and navigated the lingering divides from the 2016 campaign.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates promised voters in Iowa on Saturday they would unify the party to take on President Donald Trump even as they kept up their criticism of each other and navigated the lingering divides from the 2016 campaign.
lead_paragraph: NORTH LIBERTY, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates promised voters in Iowa on Saturday they would unify the party to take on President Donald Trump even as they kept up their criticism of each other and navigated the lingering divides from the 2016 campaign.
headline_main: Democrats Focus on Unity as Tensions From 2016 Linger
headline_print_headline: Democrats Focus on Unity as Tensions From 2016 Linger

abstract: February kicks off the presidential nominating contest for both the Democratic and Republican parties.

abstract: The inference especially is that black voters, who currently demonstrate little support for the former mayor in polling, would follow the lead of Iowa caucusgoers and rally around him.

lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Top strategists for Pete Buttigieg said they needed a top finish in Iowa on Monday and in New Hampshire the following week, but that first place was not a make-or-break deal for the campaign.

abstract: The two billionaires in the Democratic primary race are spending enormous amounts of money on their candidacies, according to new filings with the Federal Election Commission.
snippet: The two billionaires in the Democratic primary race are spending enormous amounts of money on their candidacies, according to new filings with the Federal Election Commission.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont remains a financial powerhouse, and the two billionaires in the Democratic primary race are spending enormous amounts of money on their candidacies, according to new filings with the Federal Election Commission.
headline_main: A new picture of the Democratic money race.

abstract: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
snippet: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
headline_main: Where Democratic Presidential Candidates Stand on 'Medicare for All'
headline_print_headline: Where Democratic Presidential Candidates Stand on 'Medicare for All'

abstract: The former mayor distilled his campaign message to a plea to Democrats.
snippet: The former mayor distilled his campaign message to a plea to Democrats.
lead_paragraph: WATERLOO — On the penultimate day of his Iowa caucus campaign, former Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., distilled his campaign message to a plea to Democrats: Let’s get over the fights that divided the party in 2016.

headline_main: Buttigieg warns against repeat of 2016 fights.

abstract: An Iowa Democrat asked him to look inside himself and reveal “a moment that you felt vulnerable.”
snippet: An Iowa Democrat asked him to look inside himself and reveal “a moment that you felt vulnerable.”
lead_paragraph: CLINTON — Every so often, Pete Buttigieg gets an out-of-left field question from an Iowa Democrat that’s not about how he’d beat President Trump or what he’d do to improve people’s health care.
